White House Press Secretary Robert Gibbs gave a press briefing on July 31, 2009. He discussed President Obama's upcoming schedule, including his travel plans, meetings, and events. Gibbs also addressed various topics such as the post-9/11 GI Bill, the Emir of Kuwait's visit, health care reform, the economy, Afghanistan, executive compensation, and the Cash for Clunkers program. He clarified that the program had not been suspended and that the administration was confident in the funding for the program. Gibbs also mentioned that the President had a conversation with Sergeant Crowley, expressing his wish to have chosen his words differently.